@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

 This HTML page started life as a small 3 engine page two weeks ago.
 It is now bigger and much more than I thought I would need it to be. It neatly
 fulfils my own needs and is about 50 hours of mad work too long. :)
 I don't deny writing it, but I must have been insane when I decided to
 continue. :)

 It works well on any modern browser. You are advised to use it as the home
 page, loading it from your hard drive rather than manually looking for those
 pages on the Web. The main requirement is a computer that can be on the
 net and additionally any browser that handles text (all of them!). If you're
 reading this file, there is a good chance that you can use it :) ALynx cannot
 access some of the searchers in this version. A dedicated version may appear
 in the future, if there is demand from users.

 The latest version will always be on:
 HTTP://www.geocities.com/paris/6612/amiga.html

@ENDNODE


@NODE Installation "Installation"

 Assuming the archive is already unpacked, you should move the file SSE.html
 to your fave browser directory. You can configure your browser to have the
 page as its home page. The doc file for Amiga owners is SSE_Doc.guide.
 There is also a file in HTML form (SSE_Doc.html), for all other users.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Hints And Tips "Hints"

 Using the page under iBrowse demo 1.01 is not recommended on machines with
 slower processors than the 68030. Loading the page on a basic Amiga 1200 with
 fast memory takes approximately 47 seconds. Either use a browser that handles
 text faster, or use consistent fonts in your settings - one type for H1-H6
 fonts and one for normal text. A future version may be split into different
 files, making it easier to find a specific searcher and also much faster for
 mortals like me who have their processor running at 14MHz :)

 Use the "Tab" key to move between text gadgets under MUI. Shift+Tab moves
 back. With AWeb the Tab acts a bit differently - It moves between the text
 strings on the same engine only. ALynx leaves you with many options. The
 up and down cursor keys are very effective in moving between the page's
 elements.

 Speed
 -----

 These statistics may help you find the right browser to use this page with.

     OS           Browser Name            Computer                Time Taken
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 AmigaOS 3.1    AWeb 1.2           A1200 020+FastRAM/14MHz        2.8 seconds
 AmigaOS 3.1    Voyager 1.0        A1200 020+FastRAM/14MHz        9 seconds
 AmigaOS 3.1    ALynx 1.29         A1200 020+FastRAM/14MHz        29 seconds
 AmigaOS 3.1    AMosaic 2.0        A1200 020+FastRAM/14MHz        29 seconds
 AmigaOS 3.1    iBrowse 1.01 demo  A1200 020+FastRAM/14MHz        47 seconds
 OS/2 Warp 3.0  Web Explorer 1.1d  Pentium Overdrive 63MHz        A few seconds
 FreeBSD 2.1.5  Lynx 2.5           486DX33/16MB                   A few seconds
 Windows 95     Netscape 2.0       Pentium 120MHz/16MB            2.5 seconds
 Windows 95     Explorer 4.40      Pentium 120MHz/16MB            3 seconds
 Windows 95     Netscape 3.0       Pentium 83MHz/16MB             5 seconds
 Windows 3.11   Websurf 4.6        486DX66/16MB                   5 seconds
 Windows 3.11   Netscape 3.0 beta  486DX66/16MB                   6 seconds
 System 7.5.5   Netscape 2.01      Quadra 610 w/Power Mac upgrade A few seconds

 I cannot guarantee that all servers work all the time. In fact, at any given
 time at least 3 or more searchers do not accept queries. If a searcher
 repeatedly forbids your access or totally ignores your query, please report to
 me and I will remove it from the page in future versions. It may be that it is
 temporarily down. In such a case try again at a different time.


@ENDNODE

@NODE History "History"

 Work since beta 0.6
 -------------------

 26-Sep-96
 ---------

 Version 0.65 - Added Amiga Web Directory New Links (requested by Renegrade
                of #AmigaCafe).
 Version 0.71 - Added Infoseek Ultra (suggested by Kinetik of #AmigaCafe).
 Version 0.74 - Removed a serious bug with Pathfinder searcher, that caused
                iBrowse to display weird formatting text. Also discovered a bug
                with Netscape under Win95 (still needs fixing).
 Version 0.75 - Added Yahoo (for popularity reasons). Win95 bug removed.
                Pathfinder searcher removed.

 27-Sep-96
 ---------

 Version 0.76 - A few internal conversions between tables and forms.
 Version 0.77 - Added Alta Vista and Deja News.
 Version 0.78 - Fixed a very annoying fault of iBrowse regarding a (badly?)
                written table code on the Deja News page. A new installed ISP
                Proxy server made things a bit confusing.
 Version 0.79   Fixed some minor spacing errors. A few searchers had to be
                modified as well.
 Version 0.80   Added Inktomi, Magellan. Modified Amicrawler to work better
                with iBrowse.
 Version 0.81   Improved the way Magellan works.
 Version 0.82   Added SavvySearch.

 28-Sep-96
 ---------

 Version 0.83   Added Open Text, Excite and FTP Search.
 Version 0.85   A few fixes in Excite. Added InfoSeek. Added World Wide Yellow
                Pages. Fixed a small bug in the handling of Open Text.

 29-Sep-96
 ---------

 Version 0.86   Added HotBot
 Version 0.87   Added Net Locator, LinkStar, Bookstore, Starting Point,
                MetaCrawler.

 30-Sep-96
 ---------

 Version 0.90   Added W3 Catalog. Removed Inktomi because of persistent failure
                for over a week. Made the size of the file smaller and working
                faster with iBrowse. Fixed a small bug with World Wide Yellow
                Pages.
 Version 0.91   Removed Harvest. Removed debug info. Fixed Internet Address
                Finder to work with Voyager. It would stretch the entire screen
                to both sides.


 3-Oct-96
 --------

 Version 0.92   Added BYTE Magazine search.


 5-Oct-96
 --------

 Version 1.0    Small fixes, mainly internal.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Future "Future"

 Future plans: Well, to live happily and to cherish every moment :) Ohh, and to
 make the index part guide the user to specific searchers using a smart
 recommendation system. Making the page run more smoothly is also a wish with a
 high priority.

 I will consider every suggestion by users. It is YOUR page and should reflect
 your wishes and ideas. :)

